%I A104489 #27 Jun 09 2026 18:05:40
%S A104489 1,1,3,1,5,5,3,1,9,9,11,1,5,5,3,1,17,17,19,17,5,5,3,1,9,9,11,1,5,5,3,
%T A104489 1,33,33,35,33,37,5,3,1,9,9,11,1,5,5,3,1,17,17,19,17,5,5,3,1,9,9,11,1,
%U A104489 5,5,3,1,65,65,67,65,69,69,3,1,9,9,11,1,5,5,3,1,17,17,19,17,5,5,3,1,9,9
%N A104489 Read central column in Table 3 in reference from right to left, convert to base 10.
%C A104489 There is no Table 3 in reference (?).
%C A104489 Equation (28) from the Sloping Binary Numbers arXiv paper:
%C A104489 f(1) = 1, and for i >= 0, 1 <= j <= 2^i,
%C A104489 f(2^i + j) =
%C A104489  1) f(j) + 1, if 1 <= j <= i
%C A104489  2) f(j)    , if i+1 <= j <= 2^i
%C A104489 Table 3, from the arXiv paper: f(n), ie A103318, the number of 1 <= k <= n such that k == n mod 2^k . The central columns show how f(n) is built up recursively using (28).
%H A104489 David Cleaver, <a href="/A104489/b104489.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A104489 David Applegate, Benoit Cloitre, Philippe Deléham and N. J. A. Sloane, Sloping binary numbers: a new sequence related to the binary numbers [<a href="http://neilsloane.com/doc/slopey.pdf">pdf</a>, <a href="http://neilsloane.com/doc/slopey.ps">ps</a>].
%H A104489 David Applegate, Benoit Cloitre, Philippe Deléham and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/journals/JIS/VOL8/Sloane/sloane300.html">Sloping binary numbers: a new sequence related to the binary numbers</a>, J. Integer Seq. 8 (2005), no. 3, Article 05.3.6, 15 pp.
%H A104489 David Applegate, Benoit Cloitre, Philippe Deléham and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0505295">Sloping Binary Numbers: A New Sequence Related to the Binary Numbers</a>, arXiv:math/0505295 [math.NT], 2005.
%e A104489  n | Reverse(a(n)) | f(n)
%e A104489 -------------------------
%e A104489  8 |    100000     |  1
%e A104489  9 |    100100     |  2
%e A104489 10 |    100100     |  2
%e A104489 11 |    110100     |  3
%e A104489 12 |    100000     |  1
%e A104489 13 |    101000     |  2
%e A104489 14 |    101000     |  2
%e A104489 15 |    110000     |  2
%e A104489 16 |    100000     |  1
%o A104489 (PARI) a(n)={my(i,j);if(n<2,return(1));i=floor(log(n-1)/log(2));j=n-2^i;if(j<=i,return(a(j)+2^i),return(a(j)))} \\ _David Cleaver_, Jun 09 2026
%Y A104489 Cf. A102370, A103318, A104490.
%K A104489 nonn,base,changed
%O A104489 1,3
